data.title: News from California, across the nation and world
data.meta_description: The L.A. Times is a leading source of breaking news, entertainment, sports, politics, and more for Southern California and the world.
data.text:
Live updates, news and TV schedules for the 2024 Paris Olympic Games, with track and field, women’s soccer and men’s basketball taking center stage Saturday.

Military officials rejected requirements from the California Coastal Commission for rocket launches and sonic booms as SpaceX looks to increase space rockets.

Accelerating landslides in Rancho Palos Verdes have continued to upend life. But residents like Gordon Leon aren’t ready to give up.

This week’s roundup of climate and environmental news from around the American West.

Navid Sinaki is the creative director of Cinespia at Hollywood Forever. He’s also an author. He opens up about growing up ‘quiet, queer and Persian.’

Mallory Swanson scores as the U.S. women’s soccer team defeats Brazil to win their first Olympic gold medal in 12 years and silence any murmurs of a decline.

More details have emerged about the alleged kidnapping in Mexico of Sinaloa cartel leader El Mayo Zambada by the son of El Chapo.
